<title>aria2c</title>
<p>This page explains all options for configuring aria2c in Preferences in <app>Parabolic</app>.</p>

<terms>
    <item>
        <title>Use aria2c</title>
        <p>Parabolic will use aria2c instead of yt-dlp's native downloader.</p>
        <note style="advanced">
            <p>Standaard: Uit</p>
        </note>
    </item>
    <item>
        <title>Maximaal aantal verbindingen per server</title>
        <p>This option only applies when using aria2c is enabled. This option is the same as the <code>-x</code> flag passed to aria2c.</p>
        <p>The maximum number of connection that can be used per server. Must be an integer value between 1 and 32.</p>
        <note style="advanced">
            <p>Standaard: 16</p>
        </note>
    </item>
    <item>
        <title>Minimum¬≠opdeel¬≠grootte</title>
        <p>This option only applies when using aria2c is enabled. This option is the same as the <code>-k</code> flag passed to aria2c.</p>
        <p>The minimum size, in MiB, of which to split a file. Must be an integer value between 1 and 1024.</p>
        <note style="advanced">
            <p>Standaard: 20</p>
        </note>
    </item>
</terms>
